    "18837411": {
      "title": "A tag-based noisy channel model of speech repairs",
      "abstract": "This paper describes a noisy channel model of speech repairs, which can identify and correct repairs in speech transcripts. A syntactic parser is used as the source model, and a novel type of TAG-based transducer is the channel model. The use of TAG is motivated by the intuition that the reparandum is a \"rough copy\" of the repair. The model is trained and tested on the Switchboard disfluency-annotated corpus."
